<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,311,1419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Diagnosis — Coxal field with two pairs of glandularia, PI and PIV relatively long, PV stocky.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,311,1419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">
Description — Idiosoma 810 (729) long and 527 (486) wide. Coxal field confined to ventral part of idiosoma, leaving a wide dorsal, soft area; this dorsal area without sclerites. Dorsal glandularia and associated seta on same small sclerite. Tip of first coxal plates with a pair of slender, curved setae and a pair of straight setae. Coxal field with two pairs of acetabula (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[1061,1187,818,842]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" pagination="1 - 568" refId="ref10769" refString="Cook, D. R. 1986 - Water mites from Australia - Mem. Amer. Entomol. Inst., 40: 1 - 568." type="journal article" year="1986">Cook 1986</bibRefCitation>
)(
<figureCitation box="[1203,1315,818,842]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[159,171,1810,1829]" captionTargetBox="[314,1275,411,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-2@2.[226,1329,313,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1: Oxus litoralis n. sp., holotype female: a – ventral view (Scale bar = 200 µm); b – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); c – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); d – I-leg-4-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm); e – IV-leg-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392558/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Figure 1a</figureCitation>
). Genital field 140 long, with three pairs of acetabula. Excretory pore not sclerotized. Lengths of PI-PV: 27, 42, 38, 78, 16. PI and PIV relatively long, PV stocky (
<figureCitation box="[834,942,958,982]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[159,171,1810,1829]" captionTargetBox="[314,1275,411,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-2@2.[226,1329,313,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1: Oxus litoralis n. sp., holotype female: a – ventral view (Scale bar = 200 µm); b – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); c – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); d – I-leg-4-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm); e – IV-leg-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392558/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Figures 1</figureCitation>
b-1c). Lengths of I-leg-4-6: 78, 100, 110 (
<figureCitation box="[834,947,993,1017]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[159,171,1810,1829]" captionTargetBox="[314,1275,411,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-2@2.[226,1329,313,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1: Oxus litoralis n. sp., holotype female: a – ventral view (Scale bar = 200 µm); b – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); c – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); d – I-leg-4-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm); e – IV-leg-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392558/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Figure 1d</figureCitation>
). Lengths of IV-leg-4-6: 108, 154, 164; distal seta of IV-leg-6 80 long (
<figureCitation box="[1140,1251,1028,1053]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[159,171,1810,1829]" captionTargetBox="[314,1275,411,1762]" captionTargetId="figure-2@2.[226,1329,313,1802]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1: Oxus litoralis n. sp., holotype female: a – ventral view (Scale bar = 200 µm); b – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); c – palp (Scale bar = 50 µm); d – I-leg-4-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm); e – IV-leg-6 (Scale bar = 50 µm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5392558" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5392558/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Figure 1e</figureCitation>
). Second, third and fourth legs with numerous swimming setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,311,1419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">
Etymology — Named for the 
<typeStatus box="[1212,1264,1107,1131]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">type</typeStatus>
locality being situated along the coast.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[826,1429,311,1419]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">
Remarks — Four Australasian 
<taxonomicName box="[1219,1367,1185,1209]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1219,1278,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">Oxus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
have the coxal field with two pairs of glandularia (sensu 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook, D. R." box="[826,956,1255,1279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" pagination="1 - 568" refId="ref10769" refString="Cook, D. R. 1986 - Water mites from Australia - Mem. Amer. Entomol. Inst., 40: 1 - 568." type="journal article" year="1986">Cook 1986</bibRefCitation>
), i.e. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lundblad, 1947" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1947" box="[1031,1387,1255,1279]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australicus">
<emphasis box="[1031,1187,1255,1279]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">O. australicus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[1197,1387,1255,1279]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref10914" refString="Lundblad, O. 1947 - Zur Kenntnis Australischer Wassermilben - Ark. Zool., 40 A: 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1947">Lundblad, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lundblad, 1947" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1947" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">O. meridianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[953,1138,1290,1314]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref10914" refString="Lundblad, O. 1947 - Zur Kenntnis Australischer Wassermilben - Ark. Zool., 40 A: 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1947">Lundblad, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wiles, 1997" authorityName="Wiles" authorityYear="1997" box="[1149,1429,1290,1314]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rosalindae">
<emphasis box="[1149,1292,1290,1314]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">O. rosalindae</emphasis>
Wiles, 1997
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lundblad, 1947" authorityName="Lundblad" authorityYear="1947" box="[884,1221,1325,1349]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxidae" genus="Oxus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tenuipes">
<emphasis box="[884,1014,1326,1349]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="323">O. tenuipes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lundblad, O." box="[1027,1221,1325,1349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="323" pagination="1 - 82" refId="ref10914" refString="Lundblad, O. 1947 - Zur Kenntnis Australischer Wassermilben - Ark. Zool., 40 A: 1 - 82." type="journal article" year="1947">Lundblad, 1947</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The first three species have a stocky PIV, the latter has a similar long PIV but PI of the new species is much longer.
</paragraph>
